      "writtenOn": "2020-10-06T15:53:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I remember dynamic_allocations and TSAN didn\u0027t get along, and that one needs to be excluded specifically. My only recollection of absl::Mutex problems were that we didn\u0027t like the idea of adding one more mutex class that could be used inside Skia, but I don\u0027t know that it actually caused any concrete problems.\n\nOther things I remember that don\u0027t seem to apply:\n- stack crawls weren\u0027t functional in OS X, but it wasn\u0027t breaking anything else and this could be a config issue\n- we hypothesized that it could cause problems if we were static linked into a client that included a mismatched version of Abseil. This sounds ODR-dangerous. Static linking in general seems dicey in this case unless we distinguish our copy somehow (namespace?).",
      "parentUuid": "884ade72_94bbbdf7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 11,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 11,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "276ec078de886f365ed62a7a48893801c7ce681e",
